text.section:
To the extent funds permit, the state geographer shall:
Utilize the facilities of geography departments of major universities in the state;
Advise state officials and agencies on geographic matters;
Serve as a resource for teachers of geography and for publishers of geography textbooks and atlases;
Assist state and local officials with boundary studies;
Advise state and local agencies on mapping and cartographic programs;
Assist state and local officials with planning, zoning and land-use studies;
Cooperate with other states in exchanging geographic information; and
Compile, analyze and disseminate geographic information necessary to perform the foregoing duties.
